#compdef stargz-fuse-manager
# ============================================================================
# stargz-fuse-manager - per-container-image FUSE supervisor for the stargz
#                        lazy-pull snapshotter (Go, Apache-2.0)
#
# Author : containerd Authors
# Upstream: https://github.com/containerd/stargz-snapshotter
#
# `stargz-fuse-manager` is the per-image FUSE supervisor for
# containerd's stargz snapshotter - the lazy-pull layer that
# lets containerd start a container before the image layers
# are fully downloaded by serving needed files on-demand over
# FUSE. The manager process owns the FUSE mount for each
# loaded layer, talks to `containerd-stargz-grpc` via a Unix
# socket, and maintains a bbolt-backed metadata store for the
# per-layer file-system trees.
#
# Architecture: the stargz snapshotter ships three long-running
# binaries that together implement lazy container-image pull:
#   - containerd-stargz-grpc: gRPC snapshotter plugin that
#     containerd talks to via the standard plugin protocol
#   - stargz-fuse-manager (THIS BIN): per-image FUSE mount
#     supervisor, runs as a detached child of the snapshotter
#   - stargz-store: per-layer chunk cache + on-disk store
# Plus the `ctr-remote` debug CLI for image-level operations.
#
# Flags (Go stdlib `flag`):
#   -v                       - show version and exit
#   -action <name>           - action: "start" to spawn a new
#                              detached fusemanager, or unset
#                              to run the in-foreground daemon
#                              loop directly
#   -fusestore-path <dir>    - bbolt store directory
#                              (default /var/lib/containerd-
#                                       stargz-grpc/fusestor)
#   -address <socket>        - gRPC Unix socket
#                              (default /run/containerd-
#                                       stargz-grpc/fuse-manager)
#   -log-level <level>       - logging level
#                              (trace|debug|info|warn|error|fatal|panic;
#                               default info)
#   -log-path <file>         - log file (default stderr)
#
# The bbolt lane is built on `go.etcd.io/bbolt v1.4.3`
# (declared as a direct dep at upstream go.mod HEAD and used
# from fusemanager/fusestore.go), the canonical Go embedded
# key-value store maintained by the etcd team (github.com/
# etcd-io/bbolt, 8800+ stars). bbolt is the active fork of
# Ben Johnson's original BoltDB (boltdb/bolt, archived in
# 2017 when Ben deprecated the project to discourage
# unsupported production use). The etcd team picked it up
# because they ship it as the persistence layer for the etcd
# v3 storage engine - the same KV store that backs the
# entire Kubernetes control plane runs the bbolt code on
# every node. stargz-fuse-manager uses it for the per-mount
# bookkeeping: layer-id -> mount-state, fd-id -> opened-file-
# metadata, refcount-tracking for layer reuse across
# containers.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 229 :: Embedded key-value stores (single-file ACID B-tree)
# Round 1386 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 229
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : cberner/redb                 [R1385 _sacad]
#   Go      : etcd-io/bbolt                [R1386 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : kriszyp/lmdb-js              [R1387 closing]
#
# etcd-io/bbolt is structurally the *infrastructure-load-
# bearing* canonical library for this axis - the etcd v3
# storage engine that backs Kubernetes runs on top of it,
# meaning every K8s cluster on Earth is transitively driving
# bbolt code. The fork-and-adoption pattern is unusual: the
# original maintainer (Ben Johnson, who later founded
# litestream + replicated SQLite) deprecated the project in
# 2017 not because it was buggy but because he didn't want
# to support production users. The etcd team needed a
# maintained version, forked, and bbolt has lived under the
# etcd-io org since. Today bbolt and the original boltdb/bolt
# are effectively the same codebase, just with bbolt
# receiving bug fixes + Go compatibility updates.
#
# All three lanes converge on the same architectural choice:
# *single-file, ACID-transactional, B-tree-indexed, memory-
# mapped KV store with no separate server process*. This is
# the niche that distinguishes "embedded persistence" from
# both "in-process cache" (redis, memcached) and "server
# database" (postgres, mysql). The use-case is local state
# that survives process restart without operational overhead.
# ============================================================================

_stargz-fuse-manager() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '-v[show version and exit]' \
        '-action[fusemanager action]:action:(start)' \
        '-fusestore-path[bbolt store directory]:dir:_files -/' \
        '-address[gRPC Unix socket path]:socket:_files' \
        '-log-level[logging level]:level:(trace debug info warn error fatal panic)' \
        '-log-path[log file path (default stderr)]:file:_files' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
}

_stargz-fuse-manager "$@"
